The paper focuses on analyzing the robustness and safety of deep neural networks, which is a common topic in the machine learning community. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also proposes a new technique for analyzing DNNs, which involves symbolic propagation and abstract interpretation, indicating that it may also fit into the categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Additionally, the paper discusses the implementation of the proposed approach into a software tool, suggesting that it may also belong to the categories of cs.SE (Software Engineering) and cs.SY (Systems and Control).
